<paragraph id="8BE79A75047A0D6D75C1FEAE7B87FEBA" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,646]" box="[199,989,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B92C4667047A0D6D75C1FEAE7914FEBA" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is named after the late James E. Wappes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C342C9FE047A0D6D75C1FEC27962FD7D" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE79A75047A0D6D75C1FEC27962FD7D" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,646]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B92C4667047A0D6D75C1FEC27961FE9E" bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C58E1F6047A0D6D7445FEC279A0FE9F" authority="Santos-Silva, 2022" authorityName="Santos-Silva" authorityYear="2022" box="[323,506,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wappesi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92C4667047A0D6D7445FEC279A0FE9F" box="[323,506,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Bebelis wappesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92C4667047A0D6D7704FEC27A07FE9E" bold="true" box="[514,605,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21FFB1C047A0D6D7704FEC27A07FE9E" box="[514,605,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C58E1F6047A0D6D77F2FEC27C4DFE9E" authority="(Belon, 1903)" baseAuthorityName="Belon" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[756,1047,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B92C4667047A0D6D77F2FEC27B28FE9E" box="[756,882,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">B. modesta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC9E784047A0D6D7684FEC27C55FE9E" author="Belon, P. M." box="[898,1039,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" pagination="47 - 76" refId="ref18989" refString="Belon, P. M. (1903) Materiaux pour l'etude des longicornes de Bolivie. Revue d'Entomologie, 22, 47 - 76." type="journal article" year="1903">Belon, 1903</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="136386F0047A0D6D7121FEC27CD4FE9D" box="[1063,1166,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Figs 6–8</figureCitation>
), but differs as follows: body proportionally stouter (
<figureCitation id="136386F0047A0D6D74D0FEE67A4CFE72" box="[470,534,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,679,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-232@3.[151,1436,669,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Bebelis wappesi sp. nov. 1–4) Holotype female: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Head, frontal view. 5) Paratype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886402/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); prothorax proportionally wider (
<figureCitation id="136386F0047A0D6D7690FEE67B8CFE72" box="[918,982,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,679,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-232@3.[151,1436,669,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Bebelis wappesi sp. nov. 1–4) Holotype female: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Head, frontal view. 5) Paratype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886402/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); elytra with distinct longitudinal pubescent bands in addition to the white band (
<figureCitation id="136386F0047A0D6D776AFE1A7A88FE56" box="[620,722,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[161,1430,679,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-232@3.[151,1436,669,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Bebelis wappesi sp. nov. 1–4) Holotype female: 1) Dorsal habitus; 2) Ventral habitus; 3) Lateral habitus; 4) Head, frontal view. 5) Paratype male, dorsal habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886402" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886402/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Figs 1, 5</figureCitation>
); mesanepisternum with abundant coarse punctures (
<figureCitation id="136386F0047A0D6D702CFE1A7D35FE56" box="[1322,1391,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C58E1F6047A0D6D7591FE3E7949FE2A" baseAuthorityName="Belon" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[151,275,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bebelis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B92C4667047A0D6D7591FE3E7949FE2A" box="[151,275,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">B. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the body is proportionally slender (
<figureCitation id="136386F0047A0D6D77ACFE3E7AB4FE29" box="[682,750,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[176,1414,185,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[173,1414,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–15. Bebelis spp. 6–8) B. angusta (Fisher, 1947), holotype male: 6) Dorsal habitus; 7) Ventral habitus; 8) Mesanepisternum. 9) Bebelis wappesi sp. nov., holotype female, mesanepisternum. 10) B. lignosa Thomson, 1864, syntype, dorsal habitus. 11) B. coenosa (Bates, 1866), syntype, dorsal habitus. 12) B. occulta (Bates, 1866), holotype, dorsal habitus. 13–15) B. concisa, paratype male: 13) Dorsal habitus; 14) Lateral habitus; 15) Ventral habitus. Figures 10–12 by Jesus Santiago Moure." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5886404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5886404/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), prothorax proportionally narrower (
